^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Next, let's talk about opening honor leads vs NT. They are somewhat different than leads vs suits. The lead of an Ace has a specific meaning in NT. It is typically done from a solid suit missing one honor. Often from a suit like AKJ10(...) or occasionally AQJ10(...). It asks partner to unblock an honor if he has one, usually the Queen, occasionally the King. If partner does not have an honor, then he should give count. Eddy's play of the 5 on the Ace of spades was correct--showing a doubleton. Having said that, if Nada chooses to lead spades, she should lead a low spade. With AKxx in a suit, the more standard lead in NT is 4th best.|
PG| ***** 36 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I was lucky in the hearts. Normally they should be able to take six hearts and 2 spades off the top which is the danger side of bidding 3N with Kerrie's hand. On another issue, Eddy asked me if I would open 2H with his hand, and I said no. But it turns out they can make 4H, thus proving that even Howard sometimes doesn't open weak-2s when he should :). |
